From: JosephOnuh <boldmindhub@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 2026 11:05:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(api): fluxora backend websocket updates (#49)

- Add src/ws/hub.ts: StreamHub class with:
  - Per-connection rate limiting (30 msg / 10s window)
  - Oversized payload rejection (> 4096 bytes)
  - Binary frame rejection
  - Dedup cache (streamId + eventId, LRU eviction at 10k entries)
  - subscribe/unsubscribe protocol over /ws/streams
  - broadcast() for indexer-driven stream update delivery
  - Graceful close() for shutdown integration
- Add tests/ws.test.ts: integration tests covering:
  - Connection lifecycle (connect, multi-client, disconnect cleanup)
  - Subscribe/unsubscribe delivery semantics
  - Duplicate delivery prevention
  - Rate limiting (at-limit and over-limit)
  - Oversized payload and binary frame rejection
  - RPC failure modes (hub stays up, dedup on retry)
- Add ws + @types/ws to package.json
- Document WS API, protocol, error codes, and operational notes in README.md
